video_description: Under eye dark circles can be difficult to get rid of, especially when not addressing the underlying cause. Pigmented dark circles are caused by excess melanin or pigment deposition and can be improved by using eye products with skin lightening ingredients, like kojic acid, niacinamide, vitamin C, phe resorcinol or iron oxides. Sunglasses and sun protection are also key to improving pigmented dark circles. Vascular dark circles are caused by prominent eye veins or excess fluid causing eye bags or puffiness. Caffeine, calendula and vitamin K can help reduce puffiness and the appearance of leaky or visible veins. #darkcircles #undereyecircles #darkcirclestreatment #fyp
